# ============================================================================
# AI Accounting Template — .gitignore
# ============================================================================
# PURPOSE: Keep customer data out of git. The template itself is generic and
# white-label; each customer's workspace lives in _INSTANCES/{id}/ and contains
# confidential business data (EIN, emails, phone numbers, etc.) that must NEVER
# be committed to a shared repo.
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Customer workspaces — NEVER commit
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Each _INSTANCES/{customer_id}/ folder contains customer PII (legal name, EIN,
# email, phone, bank accounts, payroll, etc.). Gitignore all subfolders.
_INSTANCES/*/
# Keep the README that explains the folder pattern
!_INSTANCES/README.md

# Exception: The fake cold-start test instance (Acme_Widget_LLC) is intentional
# demo data with made-up fields (Jane Tester, 88-1234567 EIN, .example email
# domain). Uncomment the line below if you WANT to commit it as a reference
# example for new template users. Default is to exclude even fake instances so
# nothing under _INSTANCES/ ever leaks.
# !_INSTANCES/Acme_Widget_LLC/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Customer deliveries — NEVER commit
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Zipped customer packages contain the customer's full _BUSINESS_CONFIG.json +
# rendered docs. Entire folder tree excluded.
_DELIVERIES/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pre-template legacy data — NEVER commit
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _DEPRECATED_pre_template/ is the ORIGINAL customer workspace from BEFORE the
# template refactor. It was archived locally for developer reference only and
# contains real customer PII (legal name, EIN, email, owner details). The
# knowledge has been fully extracted into generic _MODULES/ and _CORE/ templates
# — there is NO reason this folder should ever reach a shared git repo.
_DEPRECATED_pre_template/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Config files (top-level) — exclude if you've copied real data here
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If a developer copies their customer's real config to _CONFIG/ for testing,
# make sure it doesn't leak. The .example.json is safe (generic); the plain
# _BUSINESS_CONFIG.json is not.
_CONFIG/_BUSINESS_CONFIG.json

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local developer artifacts
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Editor/IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.ropeproject/
.claude/

# Python virtual envs (if anyone runs validation scripts)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
env/

# Node / npm (if someone adds tooling later)
node_modules/
package-lock.json
yarn.lock

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Logs + temp
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak
.tmp/

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Secrets — belt and suspenders
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# In case a developer accidentally creates these
.env
.env.local
*.pem
*.key
credentials.json
secrets.json
